# 🚀 What next?

🔥 Tiny improvements (high value, low effort)
1. Better timestamps

Right now:

27/04/2026, 20:08:39

Functional… but meh.

Use:

2 min ago
Just now
5 sec ago

Example:

function timeAgo(date) {
  const sec = Math.floor((Date.now() - new Date(date)) / 1000);
  if (sec < 60) return `${sec}s ago`;
  if (sec < 3600) return `${Math.floor(sec/60)}m ago`;
  return `${Math.floor(sec/3600)}h ago`;
}

Then show:

${timeAgo(alert.createdAt)}

👉 Massive UX glow-up.

2. Severity badge on each alert

Example:

[CRITICAL]
server-1
RAM usage is 86.8%

Makes scanning faster.

3. Empty state

If no alerts:

✅ No active alerts
All systems healthy

Instead of blank box.

4. Click to resolve later

Future feature:

[Resolve]

Manual ack button.

5. Subtle pulse animation for new critical alerts

Tiny red pulse dot = premium feel.

